# Security and Performance Rules

## Security

Never:
- hardcode secrets
- expose API keys
- log passwords/tokens
- commit private credentials
- weaken authentication
- bypass authorization
- trust client-side validation only
- accept raw input into database queries
- disable security middleware casually

Always check:
- input validation
- output escaping
- authentication
- authorization
- rate limiting if relevant
- file upload restrictions
- environment config
- secure error messages

## Performance

Avoid:
- unnecessary full-table scans
- loading huge files into memory
- repeated network calls inside loops
- repeated database queries where batching is possible
- large unnecessary client bundles
- expensive UI re-renders
- blocking main thread
- unbounded recursion or loops

## Logging

Use existing logger.
Do not log:
- passwords
- tokens
- private keys
- personal sensitive data
- full payment details
- private user documents

Logs should help debugging without leaking sensitive data.
